INSERT IGNORE INTO Articles VALUES (90,'David Furr - After a few classes, they were all in','<blockquote>
<p><em>"After the first couple of classes, they were ''all in.''&nbsp; At the end of the series, I was repeatedly thanked for the classes and questioned about Level II."</em></p>
</blockquote><p>All -</p>
<p>During the last quarter of 2011, our two head custodians and five of our six high school lead custodians attended the level I Building Operator Certification training held in Portland.&nbsp; The series was offered at a discounted rate via collaboration between the Oregon Schools Facility Managers Ass''n and NW Energy Education Institute.&nbsp; Yielding to my pleas, Oregon Dept of Energy also graciously contributed for our benefit.</p>
<p>Initially, the guys had mixed feelings about attending.&nbsp; Most were pleased for an opportunity to learn but there were also some reservations about the value of it, impact on their demanding work schedules, and whether they could do the classwork that would be required.</p>
<p>After the first couple of classes, they were ''all in.''&nbsp; At the end of the series, I was repeatedly thanked for the classes and questioned about Level II.&nbsp; These guys can be quite reserved and at times taciturn, and I was surprised by their enthusiasm.</p>
<p>I asked them for some thank you notes that I could send to you all, and most responded.&nbsp; They are attached to this email.</p>
<p>Most of you have little opportunity to hear from the building operators of K-12 schools.&nbsp; Their challenge is to provide safe, clean and comfortable learning environments - with ever-diminishing resources.&nbsp; The reward of this training for them is genuinely appreciated by them - and by me.</p>
<p>Thank you,</p>
<p>David</p>
<p>David Furr, CSBA<br />Utility Coordinator, Salem-Keizer School District 24J</p>
<p>1/18/2012</p>','2012-01-25 21:59:20',NULL,11,1,'2012-01-25 21:55:38',0,1539);
INSERT IGNORE INTO Articles VALUES (91,'__404__','<h1>Bad karma: we can''t find that page!</h1>
